Chinese President Xi Jinping stressed the importance of remaining committed to advancing reform, exploring new ground and carrying forward the fighting spirit to modernize the work of judicial, procuratorial and public security organs. In his latest instruction, Xi, also general secretary of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee and chairman of the Central Military Commission, emphasized that political and legal work is a vital part of the work of the CPC and the state. He said political and legal work should fully implement the spirit of the 20th CPC National Congress, uphold the Party's leadership, commit to a people-centered approach, and adhere to reform and innovation to promote its modernization. On behalf of the CPC Central Committee, Xi also extended wishes ahead of Chinese People's Police Day, which falls on Jan. 10, and encouraged police officers to make new achievements in maintaining national security and social stability. The Central Political and Legal Affairs Conference was held in Beijing on Saturday and Sunday. For the first time, the report to the 20th CPC National Congress has taken advancing the rule of law as a separate section and made arrangements accordingly.